        <abstract> 
<p>CD has only a trifling point to make in criticism [of RLT’s excerpt from <hi rend="italic">Diseases of women</hi>]: he believes "the high value of well-bred males is due to their transmitting their good qualities to a far greater number of offspring than can the female".</p> 
